---
import PageLayout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import WPPageHero from '~/components/wordpress/WPPageHero.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Postpartum Care | Mom Helper USA',
  description: 'Maternal care, newborn care, family care and housekeeping services provided by Mom Helper USA.',
};
---

<PageLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <WPPageHero title="Postpartum Care" />

  <!-- Basic Services Section -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-gray-800">Basic Services</h2>
      <hr class="border-gray-300 mb-6" />
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-gray-700 font-semibold mb-12">
        The service may vary depending on the circumstances of each household.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-8 text-[#d37643]">Postpartum Care</h3>

      <!-- Maternal Care & Newborn Care -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
        <!-- Maternal Care -->
        <div>
          <img
            src="/images/mom-holding-baby.webp"
            alt="Maternal Care"
            class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg mb-6"
          />
          <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Maternal Care</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li>Support for successful breastfeeding</li>
            <li>Breast massage to relieve engorgement</li>
            <li>Support for postpartum healing (sitz baths for pain relief and wound healing)</li>
            <li>Massage or postpartum exercise support, emotional support</li>
            <li>Hygiene management, nutrition management, meal preparation, and kitchen cleanliness</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Newborn Care -->
        <div>
          <img
            src="/images/baby-hand.jpeg"
            alt="Newborn Care"
            class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg mb-6"
          />
          <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Newborn Care</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li>Management of the newborn's room and items</li>
            <li>Recording and managing newborn activities (diapers, feeding status)</li>
            <li>Managing feeding and sleeping cycles, providing advice</li>
            <li>Newborn bathing, umbilical cord care, massages, and changing clothes</li>
            <li>Sterilizing bottles, managing breast pumps</li>
            <li>Accompanying mother and baby on outings and providing light household help if needed</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Family Care / Housekeeping -->
      <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">Family Care / Housekeeping Services</h4>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
        <div>
          <img
            src="/images/가사도우미-요리-1395.webp"
            alt="Housekeeping cooking"
            class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-semibold mb-4">
            The primary duty of the caregiver is to take care of the mother and newborn. They also look after the older child when the baby's father is on a business trip.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <li>Examples are dropping off and picking up from kindergarten (not including driving), preparing meals and snacks, washing hands and face, tidying toys, etc.</li>
            <li><strong>Adjustments to tasks can be made depending on the situation</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-12">
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-semibold mb-4">As a postpartum helper, the caregiver provides only a limited portion of housekeeping services.</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>Services may change or be omitted based on the health status of the mother and newborn.</li>
          <li>The caregiver does not support household tasks that are not directly related to postpartum care, such as preparing side dishes for other family members, cleaning the entire house, doing laundry for the family, washing bedding, ironing large amounts of clothes, making kimchi, entertaining guests, or preparing packed lunches.</li>
          <li>Additional charges may apply if household tasks not directly related to postpartum care are requested.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Basic Service Recipients -->
      <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-[#d37643]">Basic Service Recipients</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
        The basic service recipients include the mother, father, and newborn.<br />
        Additional daily charges apply for extra family members not included in the basic service.
      </p>

      <!-- Pricing Table -->
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-[#d37643] text-white">
              <th class="p-4 text-left font-semibold">Title</th>
              <th class="p-4 text-left font-semibold border-l border-white/30">Commute</th>
              <th class="p-4 text-left font-semibold border-l border-white/30">Live-In</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="bg-gray-50">
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="p-4">1. Extra Member in addition to Family Members</td>
              <td class="p-4 border-l border-gray-200">$10</td>
              <td class="p-4 border-l border-gray-200">$20</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="p-4">2. One School-Age Child (K-12)</td>
              <td class="p-4 border-l border-gray-200">$5</td>
              <td class="p-4 border-l border-gray-200">$10</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="p-4">3. Preschool Child</td>
              <td class="p-4 border-l border-gray-200">$10</td>
              <td class="p-4 border-l border-gray-200">$20</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="p-4">4. Twin/Multiple Children</td>
              <td class="p-4 border-l border-gray-200">$20</td>
              <td class="p-4 border-l border-gray-200">$40</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-4">5. Weekend/Holiday Work</td>
              <td class="p-4 border-l border-gray-200">No additional charge, calculated by date</td>
              <td class="p-4 border-l border-gray-200">No additional charge, calculated by date</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
